messages.message: Thanks for flagging, Xindi. We can keep them. Do you know how much we are spending on this? I assume that this should be a very small cost

I can't find the real cost from the billing reports. But based on this doc around oauth platform pricing, it seems to be free based on the information AIHub would request (email, name) & the # of monthly active users
https://cloud.google.com/identity-platform/pricing#identity-platform-pricing

We should move the `instabase-dev` bits to `instabase-main` (or `instabase-public`, perhaps, if it's gonna have to stick around) , and keep those auth-related pieces as the only remainder if we can :crossed_fingers::skin-tone-3:
